description: This PHP source file provides a web interface for configuring SIP (Session Initiation Protocol) settings for a Voice-over-IP service provider. It includes functions to retrieve current SIP configuration data, display it in a form, and handle user actions such as starting/stopping SIP client and applying configuration changes. The file integrates with other PHP include files for headers, headers, utility functions, and footer, and uses JavaScript for dynamic interaction.

methods.name: Dm_data_get
methods.description: Retrieves current SIP configuration data from device settings via getStr calls, returning an associative array with parameters like timers, proxy settings, account info, and SIP URI.
